# GitHub Issues Workflow

## Backlog

All work is tracked as GitHub Issues at [github.com/klexical/openRS_/issues](https://github.com/klexical/openRS_/issues).

## Labels

Every issue gets **type + priority + area** labels:

**Type:** `bug`, `enhancement`, `tests`, `docs`, `ci`, `firmware`, `emulator`, `tech-debt`
**Priority:** `P0-critical`, `P1-high`, `P2-moderate`, `P3-minor`
**Area:** `android`, `firmware`, `docs`

## Milestones

Milestones map to roadmap phases. Check current milestones with `gh milestone list` — don't hardcode them here.

## Development workflow

1. Pick an issue from the current milestone
2. Branch from `staging` (e.g. `fix/broken-can-decoder-tests`)
3. Reference the issue in commits: `fix: correct CanDecoderTest CAN IDs (refs #1)`
4. Do **not** use `fixes #N` / `closes #N` in commit messages — issues are closed manually when `staging` is merged to `main` (see `issue-lifecycle.mdc`)

## When you discover a bug or tech-debt during other work

File it as a GitHub issue with labels + milestone instead of fixing it ad-hoc. This keeps the backlog honest and avoids untracked scope creep. Quick one-line fixes are fine inline — use judgment.
